commitResults.messageTitle: Changed name from Duke to Tes
Improve on Level-1. use a new class "Ui" to perform interface interaction
Added Task class. Fix the Level-2 bug. Change storage to be storing a list of Task, instead of a list of String.
Storage class: use ArrayList<Task> to store the tasks now instead of Task[100]

commitResults.messageBody:
Instead of parsing the commands in Tes.java, add another parser class to
deal with parsing commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enable saving of tasks in the hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Implementing the feature of saving the task list into a text file in the
hard disk and also loading the task list from the respective file when
running the chatbot next time.

The format of the line shown when a task is stored has been changed to
ease the implementation of this feature.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change the way the chatbot dealing with date
commitResults.messageBody:
The chatbot now accept date in the format yyyy-mm-dd and
print in a different format MMM dd yyyy.

The task list now stores tasks with deadline dates as
java.time.LocalDate instead of string.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix the bug for Event and Deadline tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Change the loadFromFile method in Storage.java to fix the bug where
Event and Deadline will not be loaded correctly when rerun the chatbot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Include mechanism to deal with time precise to minute
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the chatbot can only record the date for tasks of type Event
or Deadline. Now, the chatbot will record time too precise to minute.

Add comments for every class, method and class member according to Java
SE-EDU Java Coding Standard.

Fix some comments written before which violated Java SE-EDU Java Coding
Standard.

Seperate the function of adding, editing and deleting tasks from
Storage class. Now, the storage class only handle saving and loading
the task list.

A new class, TaskList, is created to deal with adding, editing and
deleting tasks.

Put Tes class which is the main class to run in tes package. Add two
sub packages, command and taskmanager package under tes package.

Put Parser class, Ui class and TesException class in tes.command
package. Put Task class, TaskList class, Storage class, ToDo class,
Deadline class and Event class in tes.taskmanager package.

Use gradle to test the greet() method in Ui.java and the storeDeadline()
method in the TaskList.java

Test the greet() method in Ui.java and the storeDeadline() method in
TaskList.java.

commitResults.messageBody:
Change the plugin in the build.gradle file accordingly. Then, use
Shadow Gradle plugin to package the app into a JAR file.

Add comments on the UiTest class and the testGreet function inside.

Add comments on the TaskListTest class and the testStoreDeadline
function inside.

commitResults.messageBody:
Users can now find tasks easily using a keyword. A list of tasks

commitResults.messageBody:
Add the greeting method during initializing of the chatbot and the

commitResults.messageTitle: Add comment to new methods and classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Modify comments for some old methods too as the implementation
changes with GUI added.

Delete unwanted old codes and comments.
Delete scanner related codes in the Ui class.
Use padding on Label instead of hard typing whitespaces on the code.

In the saveToFile() method, since the tasks passed in as parameter
to be saved should not be null, an assertion is added to verify this
assumption.

In the loadFromFile() method, a record of "todo" should be split into
3 parts. A record of "deadline" or "event" should be split into 4 parts.
Thus, assertions are added to verify this assumption.
